00:20:47,400 --> 00:20:49,000
No, the system has to move.

288
00:20:49,060 --> 00:20:49,460
Exactly.

289
00:20:49,460 --> 00:20:51,800
How does the system actually move?

290
00:20:52,280 --> 00:20:57,600
How do we take an item from the hazy cloud and forge it into a link on the rigid chain?

291
00:20:58,520 --> 00:21:00,860
This leads us into the mechanics of the framework.

292
00:21:01,580 --> 00:21:05,320
What Flixing calls the three primitive operators of reality.

293
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:08,640
These are the verbs of the sphere-pop universe.

294
00:21:08,840 --> 00:21:12,980
The three primitive operators are pop, bind, and collapse.

295
00:21:13,600 --> 00:21:17,420
Everything that happens in a sphere-pop system can be reduced to these three actions.

296
00:21:18,160 --> 00:21:21,080
Let's start with the most fundamental aggressive operator.

297
00:21:21,500 --> 00:21:21,820
Pop.

298
00:21:21,920 --> 00:21:22,260
Pop.

299
00:21:22,480 --> 00:21:23,080
Like a balloon.

300
00:21:23,500 --> 00:21:23,800
Yes.

301
00:21:24,300 --> 00:21:27,220
The mathematical notation is pop sub x.

302
00:21:27,220 --> 00:21:33,220
When a system executes pop sub x on a state, it triggers two simultaneous mathematical events.

303
00:21:33,920 --> 00:21:39,340
First, it targets element x in the residual option space, omega sub t, and permanently deletes it.

304
00:21:39,920 --> 00:21:45,400
Second, it takes that element x and appends it to the very end of the history list, h sub t.

305
00:21:45,720 --> 00:21:50,920
And the absolute cardinal rule of this operator is that it is strictly irreversible.

306
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:52,900
There is no undo function.

307
00:21:53,100 --> 00:21:54,220
There is no un-pop.

308
00:21:54,220 --> 00:22:00,780
I really love the visual analogy the author uses in the text to explain this, the bubble analogy.

309
00:22:01,300 --> 00:22:03,740
It makes the abstract math so tangible.

310
00:22:04,480 --> 00:22:08,100
I want the listener to picture themselves standing in an empty white room.

311
00:22:09,260 --> 00:22:14,460
Floating in the air in front of you is a cluster of shimmering, labeled soap bubbles.

312
00:22:15,220 --> 00:22:19,780
Each bubble represents a distinct possibility in your current option space.

313
00:22:19,780 --> 00:22:24,280
Omega sub t, bubble A, bubble B, bubble C.

314
00:22:24,440 --> 00:22:26,500
You are looking at your future potential.

315
00:22:26,760 --> 00:22:27,300
Exactly.

