00:22:52,420 --> 00:22:55,020
But you cannot wave your hands and un-pop that bubble.

326
00:22:55,640 --> 00:23:00,020
Once the possibility is collapsed, the option space strictly shrinks.

327
00:23:00,520 --> 00:23:06,980
It's an evocative and violent image, which is appropriate because making a choice is a destructive act toward potential.

328
00:23:07,500 --> 00:23:11,040
But not all exclusions are violent choices.

329
00:23:11,720 --> 00:23:15,040
And that leads to the second operator, which is much more subtle.

330
00:23:15,420 --> 00:23:15,880
Bind.

331
00:23:16,080 --> 00:23:16,400
Bind.

332
00:23:16,400 --> 00:23:17,400
Bind.

333
00:23:17,400 --> 00:23:27,720
What bind does is apply an admissibility filter rule, represented by f to the option space.

334
00:23:27,720 --> 00:23:32,960
It sweeps through omega sub t and instantly shrinks it, eliminating options.

335
00:23:33,760 --> 00:23:39,660
But, and this is the vital distinction, it does not add anything to the history ledger h sub t.

336
00:23:39,660 --> 00:23:44,000
Wait, so it shrinks the future, but leaves no trace on the past.

337
00:23:44,000 --> 00:23:45,360
How is that possible?

338
00:23:45,700 --> 00:23:50,280
Because bind represents a contextual restriction, not an active selection.

339
00:23:50,920 --> 00:24:02,500
It eliminates options that are structurally impossible, contextually invalid, or forbidden by newly discovered rules, rather than options that were actively evaluated and passed over in favor of something else.

340
00:24:02,500 --> 00:24:05,900
Let's bring back our dinner menu analogy to clarify this.

341
00:24:06,600 --> 00:24:08,140
We are sitting at the table.

342
00:24:08,660 --> 00:24:10,380
The waiter hands us the menu.

343
00:24:11,080 --> 00:24:17,080
Our omega sub t is huge steak, chicken, pork, pasta, salads.

344
00:24:17,080 --> 00:24:25,820
But before we even open the menus to look at the dishes, you turn to me and say, by the way, I forgot to mention, I became a vegetarian last month.

345
00:24:26,240 --> 00:24:29,080
I have introduced a global contextual constraint.

346
00:24:29,080 --> 00:24:30,320
Right.

347
00:24:30,680 --> 00:24:32,960
That statement you made is a bind operation.

348
00:24:33,620 --> 00:24:37,700
The moment you say that, an admissibility filter sweeps across our menu.

349
00:24:38,000 --> 00:24:42,820
It instantly vaporizes the steak, the chicken, and the pork from our omega sub t.

350
00:24:43,240 --> 00:24:44,600
Those bubbles are gone.

351
00:24:44,800 --> 00:24:49,820
But, and this is crucial, that wasn't a choice of what we were actually going to eat for dinner.

352
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:52,260
It was a structural narrowing of the universe.

353
00:24:52,620 --> 00:24:55,220
And how does that reflect in the history ledger?

354
00:24:55,620 --> 00:24:56,320
It doesn't.

355
00:24:56,320 --> 00:25:07,220
When we look back at the ledger of our meal, the receipt won't say, evaluated steak, excluded steak, evaluated chicken, excluded chicken, ate pasta.

356
00:25:07,960 --> 00:25:13,040
The steak leaves absolutely zero trace in the history of our actual consumption.

357
00:25:13,360 --> 00:25:19,780
Because, given your vegetarian constraint, the steak was never a mathematically valid candidate to be popped.

358
00:25:19,780 --> 00:25:26,260
It was eliminated in bulk by a structural bind, not targeted by a deliberate pop.

359
00:25:26,640 --> 00:25:28,540
That perfectly captures the mechanics.

360
00:25:29,140 --> 00:25:31,720
Elements excluded by bind evaporate silently.

361
00:25:32,180 --> 00:25:39,100
Elements excluded by pop leave a permanent corpse in the history ledger because they were actively defeated by an alternative choice.

362
00:25:39,800 --> 00:25:47,060
This meticulous accounting of how an option disappeared brings us to the third primitive operator, collapse.

363
00:25:47,060 --> 00:25:49,340
Here's where it gets really interesting.

