00:33:34,540 --> 00:33:37,800
cost, which is denoted as L sub t.

481
00:33:38,180 --> 00:33:38,380
Okay.

482
00:33:38,600 --> 00:33:45,240
The equation governing this cost is written as L sub t equals delta omega sub t plus lambda

483
00:33:45,240 --> 00:33:46,600
delta c sub t.

484
00:33:46,780 --> 00:33:48,940
Let's break that equation into bite-sized pieces.

485
00:33:48,940 --> 00:33:51,440
L sub t is the cost of the event we just took.

486
00:33:51,840 --> 00:33:53,000
What is the first half?

487
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:54,320
Delta omega sub t.

488
00:33:54,540 --> 00:33:57,000
The Greek letter delta represents change.

489
00:33:57,400 --> 00:34:01,280
So delta omega sub t is the geometric reduction in optionality.

490
00:34:01,540 --> 00:34:06,440
It is the sheer mathematical number of futures you just slaughtered by making a choice.

491
00:34:06,660 --> 00:34:06,860
Right.

492
00:34:06,980 --> 00:34:10,020
You pop a bubble, the total number of floating bubbles goes down.

493
00:34:10,140 --> 00:34:11,580
You literally lose freedom.

494
00:34:11,720 --> 00:34:14,500
You have fewer paths available to you than you did a second ago.

495
00:34:14,700 --> 00:34:14,900
Yeah.

496
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:15,480
That makes sense.

497
00:34:16,020 --> 00:34:17,880
And what is the second part of the equation?

498
00:34:18,420 --> 00:34:19,960
Lambda delta c sub t.

499
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:26,360
Lambda delta c sub t is the auxiliary cost term managed by that accounting functor we talked

500
00:34:26,360 --> 00:34:26,660
about.

501
00:34:27,580 --> 00:34:33,340
This term captures the ethical, normative, or thermodynamic weight of the specific choice

502
00:34:33,340 --> 00:34:33,800
you made.

503
00:34:34,340 --> 00:34:38,920
Some choices are harder to make than others, even if they kill the same number of futures.

504
00:34:38,920 --> 00:34:46,380
So the total action or total cost of a history is the running sum of all these local Lagrangians.

505
00:34:46,560 --> 00:34:48,520
And once you pay it, you can't get it back.

506
00:34:48,660 --> 00:34:48,960
Never.

507
00:34:49,660 --> 00:34:55,560
And the crucial rule of the universe is that once accumulated, this action is totally irrecoverable.

508
00:34:56,200 --> 00:35:01,060
From this accumulated cost, the SpherePop framework defines a concept called conjugate

509
00:35:01,060 --> 00:35:04,620
momentum, denoted by the Greek letter pi.

510
00:35:05,260 --> 00:35:06,740
So pi sub t.

511
00:35:06,740 --> 00:35:10,040
Now, when I think of momentum, I think of mass ties velocity.

512
00:35:10,460 --> 00:35:12,220
A freight train has a lot of momentum.

513
00:35:12,440 --> 00:35:15,340
It's incredibly hard to stop or change its direction.

514
00:35:15,840 --> 00:35:19,460
What does momentum mean when we are talking about making choices?

515
00:35:19,460 --> 00:35:24,000
In SpherePop, pi sub t is defined literally as commitment.

516
00:35:24,680 --> 00:35:30,640
It mathematically measures how much of your infinite future freedom has been irrevocably

517
00:35:30,640 --> 00:35:33,180
converted into subtle historical reality.

518
00:35:33,900 --> 00:35:39,000
Every time you execute a pop or a refusal, you increase your commitment momentum.

519
00:35:39,300 --> 00:35:40,400
You become heavier.

520
00:35:40,800 --> 00:35:44,080
You become harder to deflect from your historical trajectory.

521
00:35:44,080 --> 00:35:50,280
And finally, to balance the momentum, there's the Hamiltonian, H sub t.

522
00:35:50,840 --> 00:35:56,000
In quantum and classical physics, the Hamiltonian typically represents the total energy of a

523
00:35:56,000 --> 00:35:56,320
system.

524
00:35:56,740 --> 00:36:02,500
In the psychological physics of SpherePop, the Hamiltonian represents your remaining maneuverability,

525
00:36:03,020 --> 00:36:04,560
your residual agility.

526
00:36:04,640 --> 00:36:05,600
Your freedom to pivot.

527
00:36:05,600 --> 00:36:06,240
Exactly.

528
00:36:06,880 --> 00:36:11,540
H sub t is defined mathematically as the product of your commitment and your remaining options,

529
00:36:11,720 --> 00:36:13,940
minus the Lagrangian cost you've already paid.

530
00:36:14,300 --> 00:36:18,740
Okay, let me try to translate this entire physics lesson into something incredibly human

